{"text":" Let's turn the mind towards the breathing process. Notice how the body is exhaling, inhaling, exhaling, attention on the breathing body. Watch how the body is breathing. The natural breathing process comes from thinking to breathing. Allow your body to breathe freely, naturally. The breathing body is exhaling. In thoughts arise, shift from thought to breath. Observe your breathing process from thought to breath. Back to breath. End of round 1. Prepare for the next round, in which we will shift our attention towards the breathing body. We'll begin in three, two, one. Mind on the breathing body. Observe how your body is breathing, how the air is coming out of your body, going in and observe your breathing process. Watch the natural breathing of your body. Back to breath, from thinking to breathing. to breathing body. Back to the breath. I observe the natural breathing process. End of round two. Prepare for the next round. And we will begin in three, two, one. Attention. On the breathing process of your body. Watch the exhale. The exhale. Watch how the body is breathing. Attention. I observe how it's breathing without your help. Just to witness the natural breathing. Just wait and watch your breath. Back to breath. From thought to breath. End of round three. Let's prepare and plan for the next round. In three, two, one. Mind on the breathing body. The breathing body. The inhale. Attention. In and out of your body. I observe your breathing process. From thought to breathing. The breathing body. Back to the breath. End of round four. During this break, you can open your eyes. Make yourself comfortable. Move your arms or body as you refresh and prepare for the next round. Let us prepare for the next round. Close your eyes and we begin in two, one. Back to the breathing process of the body. Attention. Attention. I observe your breath. There is only breathing. Watch your breath. Watch your breath or non-breath. Your breathing or non-breath. The breathing. The breathing body. The breathing. This is our one minute break when we refresh our attention. Prepare for the next round. Let us close the eyes and begin in two, one. Back to observing your breathing body. How the body is breathing. Attention. Attention. Attention. Watch your breath. The breathing. The air. Just wait and witness your breathing. Continue observing your breath. The air. In the next round there will be no guidance. And you will be practicing on your run with your attention on the breathing process and the breathing body. Prepare for the last sixth round of self guidance in three, two, one. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In the next round there will be no guidance. In practice for any period of time even forty seconds or one minute or three minutes or five minutes, whether you are waiting for a train or inside a bus. If you are sitting in an office at any location you can simply turn inward and practice. The breathing body and the breathing process observation. If you are sitting in an office you can time yourself to three minutes and practice in multiple rounds or even simply practice for three minutes. And if you keep practicing throughout the day you can build the meditation times throughout the day and meditate frequently. Any time anywhere. Even if you are at a restaurant or any sort of location you can step out for a moment and simply turn inward towards yourself to quickly reconnect your mind and body together. Meditate everywhere. Thank you.","segments":[{"id":0,"seek":0,"start":4.380000000000001,"end":10.14,"text":" Let's turn the mind towards the breathing process.","tokens":[50364,961,311,1261,264,1575,3030,264,9570,1399,13,51188],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.38974097796848844,"compression_ratio":0.9090909090